   244	
   245	The ``until`` method sets the jobs deadline. The job will not run after the deadline.
   246	
   247	Limit the number of runs
   248	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   249	
   250	Use ``max_runs`` to remove a job after it has run a fixed number of times.
   251	
   252	.. code-block:: python
   253	
   254	    import schedule
   255	
   256	    def job():
   257	        print('Boo')
   258	
   259	    # Run the job three times, then remove it.
   260	    schedule.every().hour.max_runs(3).do(job)
   261	
   262	Time until the next execution
   263	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   264	Use ``schedule.idle_seconds()`` to get the number of seconds until the next job is scheduled to run.
   265	The returned value is negative if the next scheduled jobs was scheduled to run in the past.
   266	Returns ``None`` if no jobs are scheduled.
   267	
   268	.. code-block:: python
   269	
   270	    import schedule

